<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,1128,1554]" box="[151,796,1128,1154]" pageId="4" pageNumber="41">Color and external characters as in generic description.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,1128,1554]" pageId="4" pageNumber="41">
<emphasis box="[197,371,1168,1193]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="41">Male genitalia</emphasis>
: Pygophore rather triangular, with distal narrow lobe, dorsal margin with setae in caudal half, setae on lobe stouter. Subgenital plate with semicircular lateral margin, with submarginal row of long setae. Apical apophysis of style expanded distally, thereafter abruptly tapered to narrowly rounded apex, ventral margin with stout setae as in 
<taxonomicName box="[549,706,1288,1313]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Platyretus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gangeticus">
<emphasis box="[549,706,1288,1313]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="41">P. gangeticus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Aedeagal shaft with dorsal marginal ridge, distally concave, shaft more cylindrical with large gonopore.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,1128,1554]" box="[197,915,1368,1394]" pageId="4" pageNumber="41">
<emphasis box="[197,367,1368,1393]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="41">Measurements</emphasis>
